<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-03-20T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-03-20T12:00:00-05:00" n="502" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2231/130: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gonzalez</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-03-20T12:00:00-05:00">March 20,
                                1937—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 5:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>17. Referring to Department’s telegram No. 11, March 19, 6 p.m., the
                            publication of the list should be withheld until I obtain acquiescence
                            on the part thereof relating to bindings which is now being considered
                            by the Department of Finance.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzalez</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>